gomodel:SYNGO_2754  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Neuroligins Interact with Gephyrin\"\nFig.2: \"The Interaction of NL2 with Gephyrin Promotes Coclustering in Neurons\"\nFig.4: \"NL2 Is Required for Proper GABAergic and Glycinergic but Not Glutamatergic Transmission in the Brainstem\"\nFig.5: \"NL2-/- Neurons in Culture Display Deficits in Postsynaptic Targeting of Gephyrin at Perisomatic Synapses\"\nFig.6: \"GABAergic Transmission and Postsynaptic Differentiation Are Perturbed at Perisomatic Synapses in the Hippocampus of NL2-/- Mice\". Experimental description: - Overexpressed NLGN2; neuroligin 2 is of rat species; \"The GST-NL2CD construct was created by subcloning the rat NL2 cytoplasmic domain sequence into vector pGEX-4T1\"\n- \"Hippocampal neurons were prepared from P0 NL2-/- mice....\"\n- \"Immunolabeling of Brain Sections: Eight-week-old male NL2-/- and NL2+/+ ...\"\n- \"Electrophysiological Recordings: All electrophysiological analyses were performed on brainstem neurons or CA1 pyramidal neurons of mice \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2754" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

